52.4	2006_Winter_Olympics	2006 Winter Olympics	The 2006 Winter Olympics, officially known as the XX Olympic Winter Games, was a winter multi-sport event which was celebrated in Turin, Italy from February 10, 2006, through February 26, 2006. This marked the second time Italy hosted the Olympic Winter Games, the first being the VII Olympic Winter Games in Cortina d'Ampezzo in 1956. Italy also hosted the Games of the XVII Olympiad in Rome in 1960. Turin was selected as the host city for the 2006 games in 1999.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/ec/Torino_2006.svg/205px-Torino_2006.svg.png
